<br>
Like someone above mentioned, you have one way to get some DPS.  Keep the shaman potions around... I see from your magelo you're 63.  Another huge piece of advice is get level 65, and get Spell: Mark of the Righteous (it's 65).  Yes, it's a magic resist based spell, but it's got a resist adjust of negative 55, meaning, it treats your target as if it had 55 points less magic resistance.  If you lead with annul magic (can dispel 4 buffs), you might also get the necro's shielding spell which has about 32 sv vs magic, and other resist buffs.  Pumice is maybe a good idea, but it's no longer instant, and you might just want to use Annul.  Anyway, mark that pet with Mark of the Righteous, and it takes 34 damage every time it hits you.  I guarantee you you can outheal that pet, while it chews itself to bits on you.  Your main worry then is keeping up with the taps and dots.  I really think Supernal Remedy for healing (1522 heal, 400 mana, 1.75 seconds) (and maybe Pure Blood, for curing DoTs) will help you out.  The darkness and funeral pyre type spells won't get cured by Pure Blood, but Radiant Cure will handle them, or just outheal them if the necro recasts after Radiant Cure.<br>
<br>
The ratio on Supernal Remedy before any AA points or Improved Healing is almost 4 to 1, whereas lifetaps are going to be significantly less than that.  Even if you use a damage shield potion, and the necro dispels you, he's probably not going to dispel his pet, and in this case, the pet's haste works against it.  Grab whichever of the armor pieces that Ragefire drops that casts the 9 point damage shield, too.  That gives you 9+32(potion at 65)+34(Mark of the Righteous) = 75 damage taken every time it hits you.  Even if he heals the pet, he's burning too much mana on keeping the pet alive, and eventually, he'll have to start deciding.  Meanwhile, get your hammer pet on him (it will use your resists).<br>
<br>
Oh and if you want to root, try Greater Immobilize or something like that, which also has a resist adjust (negative 30 I think).  So it'll land more often than root (but still might not land if his MR is high enough).<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and pets are undead... the (Verb) Undead line of spells should work, and that line resists a lot less than spells like Judgement/Condemnation.  You can always try that to help get rid of the pet.<br>
<br>
Also, I'm not sure if you have to be grouped, but if you happen to have Bestow Divine Aura, you could do a test to see if you can hit someone else's pet with that to prevent it from attacking.  If it works, it might be a good trick to give you 18 seconds to cast stuff.<br>
<br>
So, I guess if it were me, I'd probably do this:<br>
<br>
1) drink shaman potion asap, cause it's a long casting time.<br>
2) annul necro<br>
3) MoR on the pet<br>
4) summon hammer at the necro (channel it)  Mostly just to slow him down.<br>
5) melee the pet with summoned hammer... yaulp 6 for haste and procs<br>
6) use tab-1-tab to heal myself with supernal remedy.  (crits are nice too)<br>
7) pure blood myself to get rid of dots, then radiant cure for the fire/dark dots.  He may recast them.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  when pet's dead, get on the necro asap in melee (and bash) to prevent him from summoning a new pet.<br>
9) consider mark of karn/mark of kings.  Probably kings due to his resists... that's if he has a damage shield up.<br>
10) probably can't root him, but if it's a fight in close quarters where you've agreed to fight to the death, it's your mana vs his.  If your resists are nice and high, lifetaps might partial.  Might be worth keeping up DA and DB too, to make one or more spells of the necro's be wastes of mana.<br>
<br>
I can't think of anything right now, but I'd have to duel a necro or two to get some more ideas maybe.<br>
<br>
