<br>
Send pet<br>
While cleric is busy dealing with pet I annul him twice(gets rid of that pesky symbol/virtue)<br>
Then I try debuffing his poison,fire and disease once<br>
Lifetap<br>
Then a few dots some real gems here, a nice disease dot, then 2 fast acting dots, then a lifetap dot. Which basically means, cleric has to spend the time to clear 3 dots before he can touch my hp. If I have the time I will snare him, 70pct movement reduction, means he is not going anywhere fast.<br>
<br>
Your only real chance is getting resists to absurd high levels, 350+ then lifetaps is mostly resisted, disease and poison dots at that resist level is nearly usesless (the debuff is poison based so would not land)<br>
<br>
There is other tactics that can be employed by a sneaky necro, eg buffing you up against cold to fill a buff slot in an attempt to have the dots land at the end of your buffs.<br>
<br>
Oh and the arena is a bad place for a duel, littered with corpses of sk's, wizards, mages. Necro wake the dead aa ability will wake one of these corpses up to burn you to the ground. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gravely>Gravely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/23/03 3:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=77.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.visi.com/~mlm/eq/gravely_face_60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics Dueling Necros</span><hr size=1> Curious, but does Banishment of Shadows work on wake the dead pets?  Might not due to a level cap but who knows.<br>
<br>
Radiant Cure 3 is your friend in necro duels, I think, because of all the counters of stuff it cures, plus it can cure snares, dots, etc that you'd use pumice stones for otherwise.<br>
<br>
My advice when clearing DoTs would be hit yourself with Pure Blood til all the stuff with poison and disease counters are gone, then radiant cure, that sould clear snare, fire dots, and resist debuffs.<br>
<br>
Also, the more unbuffed hitpoints you have, the more time you have to react, and the more efficient your heals.  If you have 3k+ unbuffed, and have tons of healing AAs, then Supernal Remedy is going to heal something like 1800-2100 hps before crits, and up to 3915 or so on crits (with Improved Healing IV).  I would get your unbuffed hps up to the point where you can tab-SR-tab at 40% and get a full 1800+ heal every time.  With mana efficient cures for DoTs, huge damage shields, and such, you really just need to raise your mana efficiency significantly above the necro's (since they regen so much faster with lich).<br>
<br>
Sv Fire would be good for funeral pyre, too.  It's n100 resist adjust, so you'll need 200+, really.  But if you can get it past there, that's 450 mana per resist wasted.<br>
